  <h1>📰 Cybersecurity Newsfeed</h1>
  <h2>📅 08/07/25</h2>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>
    <p>Researchers released PoC exploits for CitrixBleed2 (CVE-2025-5777), allowing memory leaks in Citrix NetScaler devices. Patches are available, and admins should update immediately. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/public-exploits-released-for-citrixbleed-2-netscaler-flaw-patch-now/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>CISA added 4 new vulnerabilities to its KEV catalog: CVE-2014-3931, CVE-2016-10033, CVE-2019-5418, and CVE-2019-9621. Agencies must patch by July 28. <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2025/07/07/cisa-adds-four-known-exploited-vulnerabilities-catalog" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🕵️ Adversaries & Attacks</h2>
    <p>Water Pombero (aka Bert) ransomware encrypts Windows/Linux systems rapidly using 50 threads. Trend Micro links it to Russia. <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/cyber-risk/bert-blitzes-linux-windows-systems" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Batavia spyware targets Russian industry with phishing and `.vbe` scripts. Payloads include WebView.exe and javav.exe. <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/179699/uncategorized/new-batavia-spyware-targets-russian-industrial-enterprises.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>AMOS macOS infostealer now includes a persistent backdoor via LaunchDaemons. Targets crypto holders and freelancers. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/atomic-macos-infostealer-adds-backdoor-for-persistent-attacks/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>SEO poisoning spreads Oyster loader, Lumma, Vidar, Poseidon, and other malware via fake tool sites and malvertising. <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2025/07/seo-poisoning-campaign-targets-8500.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>BladedFeline APT targets Kurdistan and Iraq using Whisper backdoor and Exchange/IIS implants. Linked to OilRig. <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/iran-hacking-group-targets-middle/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Shellter AV evasion tool leaked and abused to spread Lumma and Rhadamanthys. Developer restricts future releases. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/hackers-abuse-leaked-shellter-red-team-tool-to-deploy-infostealers/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>SatanLock ransomware group shuts down, threatening to leak stolen data. May be rebranding. <a href="https://hackread.com/satanlock-ransomware-ends-operations-stolen-data-leak/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Monero mining malware resurges with XMRig campaign disabling AV and updating region-specific binaries. <a href="https://www.gdatasoftware.com/blog/2025/07/38228-monero-malware-xmrig-resurgence" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>📈 Trends</h2>
    <p>Popular Chrome extension “Color Picker, Eyedropper” secretly delivers spyware via update on June 27. Still listed on Web Store. <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/endpoint-security/chrome-store-features-extension-poisoned-sophisticated-spyware" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Identity-based cyberattacks surged 156%, now 59% of cases at eSentire. Tycoon 2FA phishing kit enables MFA bypass. <a href="https://www.theregister.com/2025/07/07/phishing_platforms_infostealers_blamed_for/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>💥 Breaches & Leaks</h2>
    <p>ICC confirms cyberattack during NATO summit week. Incident tied to geopolitical tensions and espionage threats. <a href="https://hackread.com/icc-contained-cyberattack-espionage-threats-pressure/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>AT&T agrees to $177M settlement over 2019 and 2024 data breaches. Claims open August 4. <a href="https://hackread.com/att-reaches-deal-over-2019-2024-data-breaches/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Call of Duty: WWII PC version taken offline due to live RCE exploitation. Flaw linked to old peer-to-peer code. <a href="https://cyberscoop.com/call-of-duty-remote-code-execution-pc-game-offline/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Chaos ransomware claims breach of Optima Tax Relief, leaking 69GB of tax and ID data. <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/07/chaos-ransomware-strikes-optima-tax.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Brazil’s C&M Software hacked via insider, causing $140M theft from reserve accounts. Suspect arrested. <a href="https://www.bitdefender.com/en-us/blog/hotforsecurity/employee-arrested-after-brazils-central-bank-service-provider-hacked-for-us-140-million" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔎 Hunting</h2>
    <p>APT36-linked TAG-140 targets India with DRAT V2 malware and spoofed Ministry of Defence site. Confucius also active with Anondoor. <a href="https://medium.com/@knownsec404team/anondoor-discloses-the-latest-componentized-backdoor-of-the-confucius-cc59ac5d1a81" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔧 Tools</h2>
    <p>Caracal is a new Rust-based Linux eBPF rootkit that hides userland and kernel activity for stealthy post-exploitation. <a href="https://github.com/adgaultier/caracal" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

